[SkillPath "competitive_bidding/lebensohl"]
[Student "S"]
{With 9 points you don't want to sign-off with 2\H. But you aren't strong enough to force to game with a 3\H bid either. So you start an invitational sequence by bidding 2NT.

Partner says 3\C.  

Now you bid 3\H. Partner will realize you have better than a sign-off, but were not good enough to bid 3\H immediately. He has a maximum, and he knows you have a 5-card suit, so he bids 4\H.}

